    "attributes": {
        "action": "Provide BSL interpretation for coronavirus briefings from the PM (in England)",
        "additional_details": "There are more than 80,000 Deaf people living in the United\r\n\r\nKingdom whose first language is BSL and so an interpreter is essential for them to understand the information being provided, and the delays with onscreen interpretation make this more difficult. Many of these BSL speakers also cannot understand subtitles. Further, if Scotland, Wales and Norther Ireland can provide this for their people, it is a shame that this government cannot. ",
        "background": "Like Scotland, Wales, Northern Ireland (and many international countries), we need BSL interpretation for coronavirus briefings, so that EVERYONE can understand Covid guidelines and current news.",
